<br>
<br>
Anyway if you cant beat them join them,<br>
<br>
DAoC wants you to get to 50. EQ does not want you to get to 60. In this aspect they are two totally seperate games.<br>
<br>
 In DAoC a level 1 character can group with a level 40 and still get exp. They want you to gain levels because only by gaining in levels can you partake in RvR which is afterall (supposedly) the entire focus of DAoC.<br>
<br>
 EQ is a PVE game. The enitre focus of thier game is to keep you wanting to get to the next level, get the next item. once you get to 60 they want you to try to conquer new zones and uber mobs etc. This is why they keep adding new expansion packs with newer and bigger mobs. IMO verant has done a very good job at keeping people addicted. <br>
<br>
 Will DAoC keep people addicted for as long as EQ? I doubt it. Thier game world is still to static, players just simply cant impact the world. even PVP gets old when it is the same thing over and over again. EQ just waits till they see people leaving the game and release new content to keep people and maybe even attract some new ones.<br>
<br>
<br>
BTW Naela DAoC does not impose penalties for camping but only rewards for not camping.<br>
<br>
Kizmet<br>
