<br>
Mostly playing a devils advocate here. <br>
<br>
It's just that so many left here (everquest, not so much E.marr) saying they were going because unlike EQ  things were going to be so much better there, things like no camping, no need for leet loot, a game for gamers by gamers (Hmm, where have I heard that before) paid customer service, even heard one person say they left because Mythic is a small company not instersted in making money like Sony *boggle at a company not interested in making money* That DaoC such an obviously better game that we were all fools for not seeing the light and running off to the &quot;promised land&quot;<br>
<br>
In actual fact I think a lot left for the new game not because of anything in the game but rather for political reasons, personal internal conflicts with other guild members or other guilds. Feeling that they were outsiders and were unable to get in with the &quot;in crowd&quot;, feeling that they had &quot;done&quot; the game, feelings of boredom with the game. <br>
<br>
What they failed to realize is you dont get bored with a game. <br>
<br>
You can get bored with the people you are playing it with (including yourself!)<br>
<br>
The ones who left expecting to find a &quot;golden landscape&quot;  filled only with nice people and friendly gamers are setting themselves up for disapointment. (No KSing in DaoC!) There was no one at the gates of DaoC stopping someone like Ewle from buying the game, and Grief payers are very inventive in finding ways of wreaking other peoples enjoyment of the game. Server dominating guilds soon cropped up and the &quot;in crowd&quot; was soon formed.<br>
<br>
other Political problems came with them too, frustrations of &quot;lagging behind&quot; the front runners, being left behind in levels or gameplay followed them from EQ. <br>
<br>
Inner guild fighting and personality conflicts followed them.<br>
<br>
They are shocked to find that the same problems that caused them to be frustrated in EQ cropped up in DaoC. why? because the same people who caused them to be so frustration in EQ were to be found in DaoC.<br>
<br>
and you know who the main source of the frustration is?<br>
<br>
Themselves!<br>
